genie (0.2.6) unstable; urgency=low

  * The 'Never mind' release.
  * Brace expansion now expands all brace groups (as a Cartesian product), not 
    just the first.  Thanks to Greg Reagle who pointed out this bug without 
    ever running the program.
  * CW Pro 6 fixes:
    - using namespace std;
    - Replace map<>::operator[] with map<>::find().

 -- Joshua Juran <jax@users.sourceforge.net>  Sun, 04 Mar 2001 04:00:00 -0500

genie (0.2.5) unstable; urgency=low

  * The 'execute' Apple event handler creates a temporary shell to process the 
    command line, making execute.{cc,hh} obsolete.
  * Bash-style brace expansion occurs on shell commands.  See the bash(1) man 
    page for details.

 -- Joshua Juran <jax@users.sourceforge.net>  Fri, 23 Feb 2001 00:00:00 -0500

genie (0.2.4) unstable; urgency=low

  * New command 'mpwsh' sends its arguments to ToolServer.
  * New command 'err2text' converts numeric result codes to error strings.
    - Proof-of-concept classes: SysErrsDotErr{Locater,TOC,Text}, ErrorTable
  * Implemented proper tokenizing and quote removal (['"\] behave as expected)
  * Began writing code to use Waypoint library instead of 
    FSSpec/FSDirSpec/pathname conversions.  Not yet tested.
  * New GenieTask methods {Get,Set}EnvironmentVariable.  Not tested.

 -- Joshua Juran <jax@users.sourceforge.net>  Tue, 13 Feb 2001 11:00:00 -0500

genie (0.2.3) unstable; urgency=low

  * Begin keeping changelog.
  * Use vector<BaseCstring> instead of char** for argv.
  * Use map<const char *, BaseRefptr<GenieCommand>> instead of if-else tree to 
    map command names (argv[0]) to handlers.

 -- Joshua Juran <jax@users.sourceforge.net>  Fri, 13 Oct 2000 22:00:00 -0400

